Christopher Stein

always curious, ever changing, grounded in reality

I teach front-end web development and design at BMCC in the department of Media Arts & Technology. A large part of my time goes into giving our students a solid, up-to-date education in modern web practices. I'm also the Director of User Experience here on the CUNY Academic Commons. You may also see me at some of the NYC Meetups related to the web.

1. Select People to Invite
X

There are two ways to invite people to the Commons:

  1. You can invite existing Commons members by name
  2. You can enter a CUNY email address

Invite by Name

Type the name or username of an existing Commons member in the box below. If you can’t find them this way you can invite them by email below and it will still work.

      Invite by Email

      Separate email addresses with a comma or semicolon, or put them on separate lines. The following email domains are allowed: cuny.tv, cuny.edu, gmail.com.
